President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Governor Jon Huntsman Jr. of Utah as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Russian Federation. Huntsman has a distinguished career as a politician, diplomat, and businessman. He has served as U.S. Ambassador to China and to Singapore, Deputy United States Trade Representative, and Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce. In addition, he has been elected twice as Governor of Utah. Huntsman currently serves as Chairman of the Atlantic Council and the Huntsman Cancer Foundation, and he is a director on numerous corporate boards.

The President also intends to nominate Hester Maria Peirce of Ohio as a Commissioner of the Securities and Exchange Commission. Peirce is currently a Senior Research Fellow and Director of the Financial Markets Working Group at the Mercatus Center at George Mason University. She previously served on Senator Richard Shelby's staff on the Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs, and she worked at the Securities and Exchange Commission as a Staff Attorney and Counsel to Commissioner Paul Atkins. Peirce received her B.A. from Case Western Reserve University and her J.D. from Yale Law School.